            <biogHist>
                <p>Christina was born to John Cameron and Cursty née Johnston in Castlebay. Little
                    is known of he early life, but she married fisherman John MacLean in 1880, son
                    of John and Flora née MacNeil.They stayed for awhile in Castlebay before moving
                    to Gearragaal. In 1891 they were shown to have four children: Simon (14),
                    William (12), Catherine (8) and Neil (6). Staying with them was an uncle Donald
                    MacNeil and a niece, Mary MacNeil, who was a domestic servant. They stayed in a
                    large croft of 5 rooms, each with windows. </p>
                <p>She died a widow after suffering myocardial degeneration and her daughter, Kate,
                    signed the death certificate.</p>
                <p>Carmichael met Christina in August 1903 where she recited a verse, beginning
                    'Raonabo cuir an t uisge os, S a leud bruich boch[d]'. </p>
